        "created_at": "2021-10-09T19:45:17.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi all!</p>\n<p>I wonder regarding the closure variants and their use from the Champagne houses.</p>\n<p>Especially the question which houses still use single-piece corks and for which bottles; Krug comes to mind\u2026agglomerated cork for the regular cuvees vs. real cork for others like CdM, CdA? DP Oenoteque?</p>\n<p>And then there is DIAM, but my question regards the solid ones - still used?</p>\n<p>Thanks</p>",
